Assignment 1 Queries

Please post all your Assignment 1 Queries as followups to this note. 

Important instruction for queries involving teams:

Conider teamid as the sole identifier for teams, and use it to distinguish teams from one another. Note that there are teams whose names have changed over the years i.e. there are multiple names associated with the same teamid. Irrespective of the name, as long as the teamid is same, it is still considered to be the same team. When asked to output teamname for such a team, output the latest name.

Important Instruction for VIews:

You are allowed to use views, we have confirmed it from sir

and hence you can write your queries in multiple lines but it should be within --q_no--

@30_f50
Anonymous Calc 4 weeks ago

14. Graph 1: The concept of graphical analysis can be applied to this dataset. Consider the tables
pitching and allstarfull. Now, we can make a graph such that all the players who appear in these
tables are nodes of this graph. The edges are defined such that there exists an edge between two
nodes (players) if they have played in the same team in the same season, the weight of the edge is
the number of seasons played together in the same team. The graph thus formed is undirected and
weighted. If players A and B played 5 games together in team X and 2 games together in team Y,
the graph will have one edge between A and B with weight 7.

Here it means A and B played 5 seasons together right ?

 0
Rakshita Choudhary 4 weeks ago
